In assessing dysphoria-linked bias in the tendency to generate emotional future TUTs involving mental imagery, to aid interpretation of valence bias scores, negative future imagery-TUTs are subtracted from positive future imagery-TUTs such that scores above zero indicate the presence of a positive bias, and scores below zero indicate the presence of a negative bias. The imagery future-TUT bias scores were computed via the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Imagery Future-TUT Positivity Bias Score }}={\text{positive}}\;{\text{imagery future-TUTs }}\left( {\% {\text{ of total TUTs}}} \right){\text{ }}-{\text{negative}}\;{\text{imagery future-TUTs }}\left( {\% {\text{ of total TUTs}}} \right).$$\end{document}Imagery Future-TUT Positivity Bias Score=positiveimagery future-TUTs%of total TUTs-negativeimagery future-TUTs%of total TUTs.

To assess the representation format specificity of observed depression-linked bias in imagery future-TUT tendency, non-imagery future-TUT positivity bias scores were computed via the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{Non-imagery Future-TUT Positivity Bias Score }}={\text{ positive non-imagery future-TUTs }}\left( {\% {\text{ of TUTs}}} \right){\text{ }} - {\text{ negative non-imagery future-TUTs }}\left( {\% {\text{ of TUTs}}} \right).$$\end{document}Non-imagery Future-TUT Positivity Bias Score=positive non-imagery future-TUTs%of TUTs-negative non-imagery future-TUTs%of TUTs.

